Usage: SET [-SILENT] [variable name] [value]
  Sets a specified variable to a given value.  If SET is used
  with no parameters, all variables and their current settings
  are listed.  If SET is used with a variable name and no value,
  that variables current setting is listed.  The special case
  value <empty> may be specified for any string variable to
  to it to nothing.  You can do:  
    HELP SET <variable name>
 to get help on individual variables.  If the -SILENT flag is
 given, then all display is suppressed for that SET commands.
